args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Fire Emblem: Kindred Ties event.
The people of this world were strong of\nspirit, and fought with dignity and bravery.
I won't let their efforts be in vain! I refuse\nto surrender to your claims of ＂fate＂!
I see. Then show me just how strong\nhumanity can be.
I'll show you all that and more!
I'll prove that fate is not absolute!
A Future of Despair\nThe Former Capital, Sol Alberia
Ngh... Wh-where am I? I remember being\ncaptured while battling Thórr, and then...
The buildings here are quite different from\nthose in Ylisse and Askr. Am I in yet\nanother foreign world?
I suppose I'll have to ask a local to know\nfor sure.
This creature seems more interested in\nmy death than my story!
What?! More?! Blast... Where are they\ncoming from?!
They are fiends, monstrous entities\nspawned by the Other—and enemies\nof all who live.
You're wasting your time trying to slice\nthrough them all. With me, hurry!
You... You don't know me? But that can\nonly mean— No, never mind that for now.
I am Zethia, princess of the former nation\nof Alberia, and dutybound to protect this\nruined world.
This is our base, the Halidom.\nWe're lucky to have made it back safely.
For the few of us remaining, this is our\nlast line of defense.
Thórr. Her merciless attacks have claimed\nmost of the lives in this world.
What?! She has come here, too?!
I take it the two of you are acquainted?
Yes. My allies and I were locked in battle\nwith her in a world far from this one.
...Forgive me, I haven't introduced myself.\nI am Chrom, prince of Ylisse.
So, you ARE from another world. That's the\nonly way you wouldn't know me...
Er...nothing. For now, let me show you\naround. This way.
Why'd we have to lose Prince\n{player_name} to the Other?\nWhy him?!
Worse yet, we're left with that awful\nempress in his place. Life's barely\nworth living at this rate!
Mommy? I'm hungry.\nCan I have some food?
Oh, dearest... I'm sorry, but I've no food to\ngive you. The fields are all ruined.
Yes. These people have endured more than\ntheir share already.
They were oppressed under the rule of the\nOther, and now Thórr too darkens their\nskies.
They've abandoned any hopes or dreams\nfor the future. I fear even their will to live\nis beginning to flicker.

It was not always this way. Once, they
knew true and lasting hope, in the form
of my brother... But he was claimed by
the Other.
I'm told those who fought beside him\nwere felled in the same fight.

And with our bravest and strongest
defeated, no one remained who could
challenge Thórr or the Other. Our world
was darkened evermore.
And yet here you stand,\ndefiant nonetheless.
I believe those of us who can still fight\nhave a duty to do so.
Well said. I imagine your people must\nagree—
What happened? She ran off as if she'd\njust seen a ghost.
Yes... She's not the first. Nor will she\nbe the last.

Though the Other currently occupies
my brother's body, he once resided
in my own—and I was a fearful tyrant
in that time.
Gods... How did you break free?

I didn't; I was merely discarded. But
while my actions are my own once
more, my people have not forgotten
the misery I inspired.
They despise me universally. But there is\nnowhere else to shelter, and so they stay.
I'm sure they recognize what you're doing\nfor them. They must.
Heh... You know, you remind me of\nmy brother.
Anyway, I don't need thanks or recognition.\nTheir safety is enough.
To that end, I will keep fighting to restore\npeace and hope to this land.
Please, allow me to lend my blade to\nyour cause.
What? Why? You aren't even from this\nworld. Surely you must worry first about\nfinding a way home?
We both seek peace for our people—and I\nwon't turn my back on your plight when\nI'm already here.
Let us combine our strength and liberate\nthis world, Princess.
